A National PDP Youth leader, Hon. Udo Okoye has been abducted by gunmen. He was kidnapped along with his son in his farm at Agbogugu in Awgu LGA of Enugu state. Okoye who was a former member of Enugu State House of Assembly was said to have gone to his farm to plant seeds with his son, when armed men invaded them and whisked them away. Would you steal from your husband?(Opens in a new browser tab) As at the time of filling this report, his abductors have not contacted his family Details later: Vanguard It's barely three days to the National Convention of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, holding in Port-Harcourt, the Rivers State capital, on Wednesday, August 17, 2016. August 14, 2016 In "News" Investigations by Sunday Vanguard revealed that the wave of kidnapping remained high in August as more than 90 people were abducted across Nigeria. September 2, 2019 In "News" The police command in Enugu State has arrested three suspected highway robbers operating along the Enugu-Port Harcourt Road February 17, 2019 In "News"